<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-70-0437 </DOCNO><TEXT>Whilst arguing for the conservation of oil and gas supplies, which shouldbe reflected in a realistic pricing policy, the options for energy productionin the long term, when these resources are inevitably depleted, are examined.Consideration is given to difficult issues such as possible climaticchanges arising from an over-dependence on low cost and highly availablecoal, the reduction of the risks and costs of nuclear energy to publiclyacceptable levels and the integration of intermittent renewable sourcesinto the existing energy system. Improved energy efficiency is seen asa priority, combined with an expanded research programme into renewableenergy sources and energy storage.</TEXT></DOC>